original_poem:
Everyone suddenly burst out singing;
And I was filled with such delight
As prisoned birds must find in freedom,
Winging wildly across the white
Orchards and dark-green fields;
on – on – and out of sight.
 Everyone's voice was suddenly lifted;
And beauty came like the setting sun:
My heart was shaken with tears; and horror
Drifted away ... O, but Everyone
Was a bird; and the song was wordless;
the singing will never be done.

Though leaves are many, the root is one;
Through all the lying days of my youth
I swayed my leaves and flowers in the sun;
Now I may wither into the truth.

translated_poem:
Si les feuilles sont multiples, la racine reste solitaire ;
Tout au long de mes jours tendres allongés
Je balançais mes feuilles et mes fleurs à l'astre solaire ;
Je puis maintenant faner dans la vérité.

original_poem:
Ten years, two-thousand stomach aches;
If I get one every other day,
Are we to have another century of guitar when the best instrument in the world is still the piano?
